# Apache Setup Pro Script

## Overview
This Bash script automates the installation and configuration of the **Apache HTTP Server** on Debian/Ubuntu-based distributions.  
It updates the system, installs Apache, configures the firewall (UFW), creates a test HTML page, and logs all actions with timestamps.

---

## Features
- Updates system packages (`apt update` & `upgrade`)  
- Installs Apache2  
- Enables and starts Apache service  
- Configures UFW firewall for Apache  
- Creates a test HTML page at `/var/www/html/index.html`  
- Logs all actions and errors to `$HOME/setup_apache.log` with timestamps  
- Captures errors in the log automatically  

---

## Requirements
- Debian/Ubuntu-based system  
- User with `sudo` privileges  
- Internet connection to fetch packages  

---

## Usage

1. Make the script executable:
```bash
chmod +x setup_apache_pro.sh

